    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_819de65b",
      "file_path": "appc-dg/appc-dg-shared/appc-dg-domain-model-lib/src/test/java/org/onap/appc/domainmodel/TestVnfc.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 206,
      "message": "You would think.  Unfortunately, Source->Format doesn't remove trailing whitespace (nor does it appear to have an option to do so).\nIt requires extra work in Eclipse to do this, including these possibilities: 1) configure \"save action\" to auto-remove trailing whitespace  2) add a short-cut key to the \"remove trailing whitespace\" action  3) configure the \"clean up\" action to remove trailing whitespace, while avoiding the other actions it normally takes",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-16 16:34:54.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_c1867e65",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_b5b7f8d7",
      "file_path": "appc-dg/appc-dg-shared/appc-dg-domain-model-lib/src/test/java/org/onap/appc/domainmodel/TestVnfc.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 206,
      "message": "Yes. I did that and it is a good practice to do so. All this are related to Eclipse.\n1. Configure save action - Just click on format the source code.\n2. add short-cut key - The default short-cut key -> Ctrl + Shift + F will format the code.\n3. Configure clean up - Eclipse default just be fine.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3813,
        "name": "Lathishbabu Ganesan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "lathishbabu.ganesan@est.tech",
        "username": "Lathish"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-17 10:05:41.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_819de65b",
      "unresolved": false
    },
